#: ../../08-append.rst:79
msgid "人民日报标注语料库（PFR）"
msgstr "People's Daily Annotated Corpus (PFR)"

#: ../../08-append.rst:81
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"PFR语料库是对人民日报1998年上半年的纯文本语料进行了词语切分和词性标注制作而成的， 严格按照人民日报的日期、版序、文章顺序编排的。 "
"文章中的每个词语都带有词性标记。"
msgstr ""
"The PFR corpus is created by segmenting and part-of-speech tagging the "
"plain text corpus of People's Daily from the first half of 1998, strictly"
" following the date, edition, and article order. Each word in the article"
" has a part-of-speech tag."

#: ../../08-append.rst:84
msgid ""
"目前的标记集里有26个基本词类标记（名词n、时间词t、处所词s、方位词f、数词m、 "
"量词q、区别词b、代词r、动词v、形容词a、状态词z、副词d、介词p、连词c、助词u、 语气词y、叹词e、拟声词o、成语i、习惯用语l、简称j、 "
"前接成分h、后接成分k、语素g、非语素字x、标点符号w）外， "
"从语料库应用的角度，增加了专有名词（人名nr、地名ns、机构名称nt、其他专有名词nz）； "
"从语言学角度也增加了一些标记，总共使用了40多个个标记。"
msgstr ""
"The current tag set includes 26 basic part-of-speech tags (noun n, time "
"word t, place word s, direction word f, numeral m, quantifier q, "
"distinguishing word b, pronoun r, verb v, adjective a, status word z, "
"adverb d, preposition p, conjunction c, auxiliary word u, modal word y, "
"interjection e, onomatopoeia o, idiom i, habitual expression l, "
"abbreviation j, prefix h, suffix k, morpheme g, non-morpheme x, "
"punctuation w). From the perspective of corpus application, proper nouns "
"(person name nr, place name ns, organization name nt, other proper noun "
"nz) have been added; from a linguistic perspective, some other tags have "
"also been added, totaling more than 40 tags."

#: ../../08-append.rst:90
msgid "生语料库和熟语料库"
msgstr "Raw Corpus and Processed Corpus"

#: ../../08-append.rst:92
msgid ""
"语料库中存放的是在语言的实际使用中真实出现过的语言材料， 语料库是以电子计算机为载体承载语言知识的基础资源， "
"真实语料需要经过加工、分析和处理之后才能成为可用的语料库。"
msgstr ""
"A corpus contains linguistic materials that have actually occurred in the"
" real use of language. It is a fundamental resource for linguistic "
"knowledge carried by electronic computers. Real linguistic data must be "
"processed, analyzed, and handled before it can become a usable corpus."

#: ../../08-append.rst:95
msgid "生语料库"
msgstr "Raw Corpus"

#: ../../08-append.rst:96
msgid "是指收集之后未加工的预料库"
msgstr "Refers to a corpus that has not been processed after collection."

#: ../../08-append.rst:98
msgid "熟语料库"
msgstr "Processed Corpus"

#: ../../08-append.rst:99
msgid "相对而言，熟语料库就是经过加工的"
msgstr "Relatively, a processed corpus is one that has been handled."

#: ../../08-append.rst:102
msgid "标记说明"
msgstr "Tag Description"

#: ../../08-append.rst:104
msgid "标记说明参考："
msgstr "Tag description reference:"

#: ../../08-append.rst:156
msgid "from: https://cloud.tencent.com/developer/article/1091906"
msgstr "from: https://cloud.tencent.com/developer/article/1091906"

#: ../../08-append.rst:159
msgid "格式说明"
msgstr "Format Description"

#: ../../08-append.rst:161
msgid "语料是纯文本文件，文件中每一行代表一自然段或者一个标题， 一篇文章有若干个自然段， 因此在语料中一篇文章是由多行组成的。"
msgstr ""
"The corpus consists of plain text files, where each line represents a "
"paragraph or a title. An article has several paragraphs, so an article in"
" the corpus is composed of multiple lines."

#: ../../08-append.rst:163
msgid ""
"每一行的开头是编号。 比如 ``19980101-01-001-001`` "
"表示这一自然段是1998年1月1日的第01版的第001篇文章的第001自然段， 用短横线隔开的4部分按照顺序是“年月日-版号-篇章号-段号”。 "
"标号也作为一个词进行标注，词性固定为“m（数词）”。"
msgstr ""
"The beginning of each line is a serial number. For example, "
"``19980101-01-001-001`` indicates that this paragraph is the 001st "
"paragraph of the 001st article in the 01st edition on January 1, 1998. "
"The four parts separated by hyphens are \"YearMonthDay-Edition-Article-"
"Paragraph\". The serial number is also tagged as a word, with the fixed "
"part of speech \"m (numeral)\"."

#: ../../08-append.rst:166
msgid ""
"一篇文章里面的段落之间是不空行的，在两篇文章之间，会有一个空行，表示文章的分界线， 同时，下一篇文章的“篇章号-段号”都会有所改变。 "
"标号之后，是2个单字节空格，然后开始正文。"
msgstr ""
"There are no empty lines between paragraphs within an article. Between "
"two articles, there is an empty line to indicate the boundary. At the "
"same time, the \"Article-Paragraph\" numbers of the next article will "
"change. After the serial number, there are 2 single-byte spaces, followed"
" by the main text."

#: ../../08-append.rst:169
msgid ""
"正文部分按照规范已经切分成词，并且加上标注， 标注的格式为“词语/词性”，即词语后面加单斜线，再紧跟词性标记。 "
"词与词之间用2个单字节空格隔开。每段最后的词，在标记之后也有2个单字节空格，保持格式一致。 语料中除了词性标记以外，还有“短语标记”， "
"这种情况一般出现在机构团体名称、成语等情况中。"
msgstr ""
"The main text has been segmented into words according to specifications "
"and annotated. The annotation format is \"word/POS\", i.e., a single "
"slash after the word followed by the POS tag. Words are separated by 2 "
"single-byte spaces. The last word of each paragraph also has 2 single-"
"byte spaces after the tag to maintain consistent formatting. In addition "
"to POS tags, there are also \"phrase tags\" in the corpus, which usually "
"appear in organization names, idioms, etc."

#: ../../08-append.rst:173
msgid ""
"如“通过/p [中央/n 人民/n 广播/vn 电台/n]nt 、/w”中， 用“[ ]”合起来的部分是一个完整的机构团体名称， "
"方括号后面紧跟标注 ``nt`` ，\\ ``nt`` 之后空两个单字节空格，保持了格式的一致。"
msgstr ""
"For example, in \"通过/p [中央/n 人民/n 广播/vn 电台/n]nt 、/w\", the part combined "
"with \"[ ]\" is a complete organization name, followed by the tag ``nt``."
" After ``nt``, there are two single-byte spaces, maintaining format "
"consistency."

